er version of [[The Beatles]]' \"[[Let It Be (Beatles song)|Let It Be]]\" was the first recording of the song to be commercially issued (The Beatles did not release \"Let It Be\" as a single until March 1970). Songwriter [[Paul McCartney]] sent Franklin and Atlantic Records a demo of the song as a guide.<ref name=\"Let Beatles\"/>\n\n==Track listing==\nInformation is based on the album's Liner Notes<ref name=\"Rhino Girl\"/><ref name=\"Girl Love\">Franklin, Aretha.  \"This Girl's In Love with You\" (Original Album Notes).  Atlantic.   1970.  </ref>\n#\"[[Son of a Preacher Man]]\" ([[John Hurley and Ronnie Wilkins|John Hurley]], [[John Hurley and Ronnie Wilkins|Ronnie Wilkins]]) \u2013 3:19\n#\"[[Share Your Love with Me]]\" (Al Braggs, [[Don Robey|Deadric Malone]]) \u2013 3:21\n#\"[[The Dark End of the Street]]\" ([[Chips Moman]], [[Dan Penn]]) \u2013 4:42\n#\"[[Let It Be (Beatles song)|Let It Be]]\" ([[John Lennon]], [[Paul McCartney]]) \u2013 3:33\n#\"[[Eleanor Rigby]]\" (John Lennon, Paul McCartney) \u2013 2:38\n#\"[[This Guy's in Love with You|This Girl's in Love with You]]\" ([[Burt Bacharach]], [[Hal David]]) \u2013 4:00\n#\"It Ain't Fair\t\" ([[Ron Miller (songwriter)|Ronnie Miller]]) \u2013 3:22\n#\"[[The Weight]]\" ([[Robbie Robertson]]) \u2013 2:59\n#\"[[Call Me (Aretha Franklin song)|Call Me]]\" (Aretha Franklin) \u2013 3:57\n#\"Sit Down and Cry\" ([[Clyde Otis]], Lou Stallman) \u2013 3:52\n\n==Personnel==\nInformation is based on the album's Liner Notes<ref name=\"Rhino Girl\"/><ref name=\"Girl Love\"/>\n;Main Performance\n*[[Aretha Franklin]] \u2013 vocals (4, 6, lead on 1-3, 5, 7-10), acoustic piano, additional keyboards\n*[[Duane Allman]] \u2013 slide guitar, steel guitar (7-8)\n*Brenda Bryant \u2013 background vocals (9)\n*[[Cissy Houston]] \u2013 background vocals (8-10)\n*[[King Curtis]] \u2013 tenor saxophone (2, 7-8)\n*Pat Lewis \u2013 background vocals (9)\n*Sylvia Shemwell \u2013 background vocals (8, 10)\n*[[The Sweet Inspirations]] \u2013 back